#Text=Prevent Major Home Repairs

#Text=Just as a routine maintenance schedule helps prevent major repairs to your car , and just as regular visits to a doctor can help prevent illnesses and afflictions from developing , routine maintenance of your home can help you ward off major , costly repairs .
#Text=Paying for home repairs out of pocket is one of the unpredictable and less glamorous aspects of home ownership .
#Text=Major repairs , up to and including structural damage , can be inaccessibly expensive .
#Text=To help prevent major home repairs , it helps to practice routine maintenance of your home .
#Text=The guide below highlights some of the important aspects of this maintenance .
#Text=Steps
#Text=Clean your gutters regularly .
#Text=This is one of the most important tasks in warding off major home repairs .
#Text=Gutters are designed to direct water safely away from your home .
#Text=When they are clogged with leaves and debris , water overflows out of the gutters directly onto the ground surrounding your house .
#Text=This can quickly saturate the soil against your home 's foundation , which can lead to leaky basement walls and even cracked concrete foundations .
#Text=Change your home 's air filters regularly .
#Text=Dirty air filters not only impede the flow of air through your home ; they can cause major damage to your air conditioning unit .
#Text=Inadequate air flow across the unit 's evaporator coil can cause the temperature to drop enough for ice to form on the coils .
#Text=This ice can eventually crack or collapse the tubing in the evaporator coil , which would require a costly visit from an HVAC technician .
#Text=Keep a vigilant eye out for mold growth .
#Text=Mold and mildew growth is fairly common in homes , as mold only needs some organic material and a bit of moisture to proliferate .
#Text=In areas where moisture levels are high ( typically bathrooms and kitchens ) , regularly scrub walls , ceilings , and fixtures with bleach , vinegar , or another disinfectant .
#Text=Letting mold growth proceed unchecked can quickly cause damage to the studs in your walls , which will require major and costly structural repairs .
#Text=Replace aging or malfunctioning appliances or fixtures .
#Text=Aging and faulty electrical wiring can pose a risk of fire .
#Text=Old appliances should be inspected by an electrician and replaced or reconditioned when no longer in safe condition .
#Text=Any wiring in your home with stripped or frayed insulation should be replaced immediately .
#Text=Small fixtures like lamps can usually be completely rewired with little trouble .
#Text=An electrical fire can very easily get out of control and cause major structural damage .
#Text=Take precautions against insect infestations .
#Text=Insects can cause major damage to your home , but even when they do not cause structural damage , they can be very expensive to eliminate .
#Text=Insects such as termites , roaches , and bed bugs can be kept ay bay by making sure that your house is cleaned regularly .
#Text=Avoid eating food throughout your home , instead eating only in your kitchen or dining area .
#Text=Being vigilant about water damage will also help prevent termites and other insects that feed on water-softened wood .
#Text=Tips
#Text=Purchasing comprehensive homeowner 's insurance is another effective strategy for mitigating the out-of-pocket cost of major home repairs .
#Text=Remember that fire and flood damage may need to be covered through a separate policy .
